l administrators, welfare providers and welfare recipients, and the respectable and non-respectable. Topics covered include the politicisation of the welfare system, the relief of distress, the provision of labourers’ cottages and the role of women in poor law administration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aPoor lawsxHistoryx19th centuryxIreland. 0aPoor lawsxPolitical aspectsxIreland. 0aPoor lawsxPolitical aspectszIreland. 0aPoor lawsxSocial aspectsxIreland. 0aPoor lawsxSocial aspectszIreland. 0aPoor lawszIrelandxHistoryy19th century. 0aPoorxHistoryx19th centuryxIreland. 0aPoorzIrelandxHistoryy19th century. 0aPovertyxHistoryx19th centuryxIreland. 0aPovertyzIrelandxHistoryy19th century. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aEvicted Poor Protection Act.  aGreat Famine.  aIrish nationalism.  aIrish poor law system.  aboard nationalisation.  alabourers acts.  aland campaign.  anationalist guardians.  anineteenth-century Ireland.  apauperism.  apolitical community.  apolitics.  apoor law administration.  apost-famine period.  arelief system.  awelfare services.1 aCrossman, Virginia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129611/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013